Package edu.jsu.mcis

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Argument
    Argument is an abstract class that includes argument name, description, value set, value and argument type.
    ArgumentParser
    This class parses an object (argument) and stores the value for user purposes
    NamedArgument
    Named argument is an argument object that takes a name rather than a position.
    PositionalArgument
    Class positional argument creates a required argument to be read from the command line in a specified order.
    XMLReader
    XMLReader allows for reading of an XML file which holds program information and argument information.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Argument.ArgType  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ArgumentDoesNotExistException
    Thrown to indicate that an argument called from the command line has not been created
    HelpException
    Thrown to display a list of availbale options for the user.
    IncorrectArgTypeException
    Thrown to indicate that an argument type expected is different from argument type given.
    IncorrectArgumentValueException
    Thrown to indicate that a given argument value is not a possible value for that argument.
    IncorrectNumberOfArgsException
    Thrown to indicate that there are either too many or not enough arguments given than expected.
